INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (120001, 'I hold the memories of you in my heart.', 2878, 0), (120002, 'I can''t give you my beating heart, but I can give you my unconditional love.', 2876, 0), (120003, 'May the stars guide you on your journey, and your heart always lead you home.', 23291, 0), (120004, 'Once I had a love affair with myself.I was left heart broken.', 2876, 0), (120005, 'His hand reached up to his chest and rubbed at the area over his heart as if it hurt him.', 811, 0), (120006, 'In their minds, it seems as though people don''t often have the same answers, but in their hearts, they do very frequently have the same questions.', 230, 0), (120007, 'A torpid heart in agony needs a pen to bleed', 2760, 0), (120008, 'On the surface, I seem to be glad of new people;But doomed to leave old friends behind me,I cry out from my heart for Shin-Fêng wineTo melt away my thousand woes.', 23292, 0), (120009, 'Heart’s fragrance is spent with the ending of springAnd nothing left but a tear-stained robe.', 23292, 0), (120010, 'I think it’s the whole ‘bad boy who’s so good but destined to break your heart’ fantasy. Which doesn’t sound like much of a fantasy when you put the broken heart part in the picture, but it is. It so is.', 12051, 0), (120011, 'My heart is my home.', 2878, 0), (120012, 'Then her heart opened wider than it ever had before, and all she saw before her, everywhere she looked, were people to love.', 5066, 0), (120013, 'Dear God, I ask that you help me with the darkness I’ve been feeling and that you help me make today a changing day in my life. I ask you, dear God, for calm in my mind and your light in my heart. I ask these things in Jesus’s name, amen.', 5082, 0), (120014, 'We are each given a life to show what we can achieve during our time here on Earth.And we are each given a heart to show how we can be compassionate and kind during our time here on Earth.We shouldn''t waste either.', 2876, 0), (120015, 'My heart is my heavenly home.', 2878, 0), (120016, 'Silence is golden, but saying, "I Love You."Is priceless.', 23293, 0), (120017, 'The heart was designed to worship, and if it is not being utilized to worship God, it will worship something else.', 23294, 0), (120018, 'Wherever, I am, you will always be in my heart.', 2878, 0), (120019, 'Where''s the heart?" - Dimitri Belikov', 83, 0), (120020, 'When love fills your heart, all bridges lead to something wonderful. (All roads and tunnels too!)', 5066, 0), (120021, 'Your heart beats against the palm of my hand.Its need to beOne with meDripsBetween my fingertipsAs I squeeze perfect drops of love into small receptacles to be preserved...For later. ☕️', 7585, 0), (120022, 'There was nothing special with the way he looked at her but her heart raced even with a glance.', 7743, 0), (120023, 'Life’s journey is a narrow path that reveals a God to trust. Few take it. Trust only occurs in relationship. Our relationship is the pearl of great price that is already buried in the field of our hearts. The journey is the life-long excavation of our heart.', 10817, 0), (120024, 'There was nothing special with the way he looked at her but her heart raced with even glance.', 7743, 0), (120025, 'Into the sea I’d love to sink When with both eyes a shark can blinkIs he a brave fish or a marine man?Through those closed eyelids my heart will he scan?', 2760, 0), (120026, 'My life is never empty because my heart is always full.', 2876, 0), (120027, 'Just because you haven''t got a home, doesn''t make you homeless.andJust because you don''t have a heart, doesn''t make you heartless.Now, does it?', 2876, 0), (120028, 'Heaven lies in the heart.', 2878, 0), (120029, 'A flicker of defiance flared very briefly in Rincewind''s battered heart.', 195, 0), (120030, 'The key to the world is the key to your self and the key to yourself is the key to the world.', 5745, 0), (120031, '. . . Like ashes of gold in a cinnamon-flame,My youthful desires have been burnt with the years– And tonight in the chilling sunset-windA cicada, singing, weighs on my heart.', 23295, 0), (120032, 'The sick constriction of the heart was undeniable; there was a melancholy truth in the fact that it was suffering which made me, I thought, at last real to myself.', 21367, 0), (120033, 'Matters of the heart were important, but people tended to put too much stock in the particular organ when, in retrospect, it was only tissue. It pumped blood and the body couldn’t live without it, sure, but it had no actual bearing on love. The soul was what made a person distinct—the part that lived on after death, how one being connected to another, and what bound essence.', 6448, 0), (120034, 'The female warrior knows how to fight without violence. She knows when not to raise her sword, but instead hold up her heart. Her shield is not a defense against others but a shelter for all.', 23296, 0), (120035, 'Watch them describe you to somebody else and see how it long it takes for them to bring up your physical description that''ll tell you all.', 8426, 0), (120036, 'What is the one message that only you can give? It''s your story.', 9207, 0), (120037, 'We overestimate what we hear from others, what the facts may be. But the truth, it always lies in our hearts. When you choose the right person to love, you’re happy. Even after one or two failed attempts, when there are obstacles in the way, soon enough things have a way of working out. But if you’ve tried all you could, and you’re still suffering, then it’s time to let go. Just ask your heart. If the pain is more than you can handle, then it’s time to move on', 12948, 0), (120038, 'Be still my little light beam,As I breathe life into your heart,By giving you the essence of color,To show off your blossoming heart.In its red gentleness,I see your flickering flame,And then I see your body,Glowing in the dusk.Ever so gently,You do but come to life,For me to see your entirety,For me,It’s the color of love.', 23297, 0), (120039, 'Believe in YourselfWhy must we see something to believe in its existence?The wind itself cannot be seen by man, but all have felt it''s gentle touch and watched the mighty trees bow as it swept past.We cannot see love yet its nurturing warmth is the essence of our being and sorrow can touch our very soul.  For remorse is like a ripple on the ocean, once given it remains only in the heart of the receiver.Yet all of these cannot be seen only felt. Why then do you doubt your self-worth? For though it cannot cast a reflection in the mirror you have only to look in the eyes of those you love toSee it clearly.Prologue To Kiss a KingTo Kiss a King Copyright © 2017 by Julie Brookshier and Robin WoodsAll rights reserved. Except for use in a review, the reproduction or use of this work in whole or in part in any form is forbidden without written permission of one or more of the authors.This is a fictional work. Names, characters, places, and events are merely the product of the authors'' imaginations or used fictitiously, purely for entertainment purposes. Any resemblance to actual persons, living, dead, or undead or any business establishments, events or places past, present, or future, is entirely coincidental.', 7142, 0), (120040, 'And suddenly there came a second, when somehow for the first time I saw (as if a door had opened from a dark room into the sunny street), and in the next second I already knew for sure that God exists and that God is the Jesus Christ of Orthodoxy, and not some other God. I call this moment the greatest miracle because this precise knowledge came to me not through reason (I know this for sure) but by some other way, and I am unable to explain this moment rationally ....', 3068, 0), (120041, 'One of the scariest things in the world, is that other people can make life-changing decisions for you.', 8426, 0), (120042, 'If your heart doesn''t judge you anything, fear neither God nor Devil therefore, Don''t judge yourself for nothing just keep on trying to do your best.', 12287, 0), (120043, 'That''s the problem with getting your heart wrapped up in things. The dumbest stuff starts to carry way too much significance. You think about things way too much. You imagine a hole being filled that rarely bothered you at all when it was empty.', 6276, 0), (120044, 'There exist love in every heart.', 2878, 0), (120045, 'All I wanted was you. I tore down my wall for you. Now it''s been rebuilt.', 11857, 0), (120046, 'A person may only touch one person''s heart.A rainbow touches many.', 2876, 0), (120047, 'They say the heart is just a muscle. They say it plays absolutely no role in our emotions and that its use as a symbol for love is based on archaic theories of it being the seat of the soul or something ridiculous like that. But as I quietly listened to every word she was saying to me, as each syllable shot a sharp arrow through the phone and into my ear, I swear I felt like my entire chest would collapse in on itself. I knew this feeling. They say a heart can''t really break because there''s nothing to be broken. But see, I once had to leave everyone I loved, and it felt this same way.', 1591, 0), (120048, 'My heart is my best asset, my heart is my biggest liability.', 15044, 0), (120049, 'Often the heart can see what the eyes cannot.', 6353, 0), (120050, 'The sacred fire burns in our heart.', 2878, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (120051, 'Your intuition speaks on a higher plane than anything you’ll ever grasp.', 3805, 0), (120052, 'My heart is a harness of nothing, deflated balloon, and a place of loss.', 7537, 0), (120053, 'Again and again I asked for permission. May I? Here? And here? Is this too much? Too little? Can you hear me? This is my heart.', 23298, 0), (120054, 'There is nothing like passion. The fire that burns in our heart.', 2878, 0), (120055, 'I told you this would never be easy, I warned you. I begged you to spare my heart if you weren’t ready for this fight.', 12176, 0), (120056, 'To love one must focus one''s heart on another.', 3544, 0), (120057, 'Let the heart be thy heavens.', 2878, 0), (120058, 'Prayer is not a court hearing, so when you pray don''t aim to prove before God how others wronged you; because He knows every heart already.', 5160, 0), (120059, 'Every time you hurt my heart, you are actually making it stronger than before.', 5160, 0), (120060, 'He hasn''t earned your your mercy."Nessy replied, "Mercy isn''t earned. It''s given.', 9885, 0), (120061, 'A heart is all that didn''t get removed.', 3544, 0), (120062, 'There''s a certain charm to fragile hearts❤', 8426, 0), (120063, '...Cause the heart has no manual settings.', 8426, 0), (120064, 'If you''ve never gotten your heart broken, you''ve not used it well.', 8426, 0), (120065, 'If you believe only in facts and forget stories, your beain will live, but your heart will die', 39, 0), (120066, 'It takes love to hold on when you want to let go. It takes love to let go when you want to hold on.', 9420, 0), (120067, 'Every day, let our words blossom lotus in some one''s heart.', 379, 0), (120068, 'I may not have a world of things, I may not have the biggest wings, What I do have is a heart of love, Because I trust the One above', 15872, 0), (120069, 'While we tediously check our weaponry before entering into battle, do we check our hearts? For without exception, that is the greatest weapon of all.', 4397, 0), (120070, 'Despite how utterly massive they might be, it is never the size of the arsenal nor the strength of the warrior. Rather, it is a heart bent on sacrifice that is the most potent weapon of all.', 4397, 0), (120071, 'Giving away the very last peace of our heart is foolish! But if we keep it to ourselves might be selfish as well...so i think we should stay committed to the decisions and be flexible in our approach for a better result (Ejump,2017)', 6310, 0), (120072, 'If you are near ,my heart beats fast,If you are far, my hearts becomes restless,When you look at me,my world stops,When you look away i wish the world to stop.I can die to see your smile,I die as i see your tears.When i see you my mind floods,When i don''t it gets a drought.', 7545, 0), (120073, 'Great emotional singing isn''t a destination, it''s a journey, one to be taken time and again to different places with different moods and different audiences.', 15892, 0), (120074, 'It is not the job of the intellect to tame the passions of the heart, that is the job of the spirit. The intellect is best managed by the heart, without this connection you get the psychopath. The heart is best managed by the spirit, without this connection, you get the horrors of war.', 7501, 0), (120075, 'remember,it''s not what one wears or has in one''s pocketrather it''s what''s in the heart andthe kindness that brings forth..LT', 20483, 0), (120076, 'A full heart has more room than an empty one.', 5148, 0), (120077, 'The ears and the heart are connected, it’s true,for when ears open wide, the heart opens up too.', 1456, 0), (120078, 'Once a thing is removed from your heart, a trace of it still remains.', 3544, 0), (120079, 'Bringing countries together above their conflicts require great minds and great hearts.', 379, 0), (120080, 'The way to my heart is through your heart.', 884, 0), (120081, 'Time Can Not Cure Heart''s Wounds Never,But Wounds Spoil and Kill Heart On The Time', 6292, 0), (120082, 'If metal can be polishedto a mirrorlike finish,what polishing might the mirrorof the heart require?Between the mirror and the heartis this single difference:the heart conceals secrets,while the mirror does not.', 58, 0), (120083, 'You are the sole owner of your heart, so be careful of whom you give access to.', 5160, 0), (120084, 'The inner thought coming from the heart represents the real motives and desires.', 23299, 0), (120085, 'We all want to look good, but genuine goodness is in the heart.', 5160, 0), (120086, 'Her heart felt too full, a dry creek bed ill-prepared for such rain.', 361, 0), (120087, 'But is it not a sort of genius to cut always to the heart? ', 272, 0), (120088, 'Love is for the birds.Honey is for the bees.And you, my special one.Are the only one for me.', 2876, 0), (120089, 'Your smile breaks my heart,And your laughter burns my skin,And if I had to tell you how I feel,That''s where I''d begin.', 7562, 0), (120090, 'Because at that moment, with the press of Rahim''s lips to hers, with the touch of his tongue sending wildfire through her veins, she knew she would always be home here.  With this boy. In this moment. In this time. And that her heart would never be lonely again.', 333, 0), (120091, 'Such a nasty bruise,” he says, staring straight into my eyes. I am stunned he can see it. Delicate to the touch and tender on every side, the bruise is deeper than days. My hand automatically moves to my chest.Science taught me with valid assurance that my heart was fixed in my rib cage, but life has since shown me otherwise. My heart in fact dangles from a tangle of strings. The ends are grasped tight by numerous people who yank and release, having caused many painful bruises over time. I cry because they are invisible to most.“Such a nasty bruise,” he repeats, tugging on my poor heart. His kind eyes fall away from mine as I feel a squeeze on my arm. He twists it enough to show me a small, round patch of purple surrounded by a sickly yellowish corona. “Oh. My elbow.” I let the air exhale from my lungs. Another bruise forms where my heart has hit the floor. It is jerked up again. “Can I do anything for you?” I see in his eyes the mirror image of a finger—his finger—wrapped in one of the dangling strings. He tugs and I feel it.“No,” I reply to his question. But it is a lie. There is something he could do, along with all who grasp a portion of the web entangling my heart. I wish they would mercifully let go.', 1456, 0), (120092, 'Rachel drank some more bourbon. “What I am trying to do,” she said, “is tothank you. And to say it as genuinely as I can. I do thank you. I will remember aslong as I live when you came into the room and got me, and I will alwaysremember when you killed them, and I was glad, and you came and we put ourarms around each other. And I will always remember that you cried.', 10827, 0), (120093, 'I have seen so many lands vanish in my wake, torn down like stage sets. What survives of them? An image as fleeting as a dream: whatever beauties I discovered, I already knew by heart.', 16473, 0), (120094, 'Writing is not just my Hobby . Pen is mouthpiece of my feelings,I have no another one But paper is my best friend. and My Best Friend always Listen so patiently whatever,whenever i speak', 6292, 0), (120095, 'Last night the nightingale sat by my window and sang her joyous song of love...Though I loved it, my heart silently missed the beautiful song of your heart beat!', 5535, 0), (120096, 'You cannot conquer the mind of a man, if you do not know his heart and you cannot win over his heart, if so you do not know his mind.', 7581, 0), (120097, 'He came to the conclusion that it was because there were some things you remembered with your head, like numbers, and other things you remembered with your heart, like shapes, colours, and shadows. He was a heart-memory type.', 23300, 0), (120098, 'When we open our hearts to the breadth of our experiences, we learn to tune into our needs, unique perceptions, thoughts & feelings', 124, 0), (120099, 'Huang Sung turned to the master and asked, "Master, will it come to pass?"The master looked up into the sky and then turned to Huang Sung, "When the sky is red from our tears and the earth is blackened by the ashes of our forefathers and then, when we look inwards to where our hearts once were, then we shall know that it has come to pass, but not in the time allotted to man."From a book that I am writing, called, "The Teachings of Huang Sung.', 2876, 0), (120100, 'I loved her. I did not know what state of mind I would be in when I got where I was going and I was most worried that in the process I might forget her. I did not ever want to forget her! I held the image of her in my mind so strongly and the eternal love for her so deep within my heart that it could never ever be erased, no matter what. My love for her was stronger than anything that could happen to me.', 9420, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (120101, 'No one is truly literate who cannot read his own heart.', 2567, 0), (120102, 'What one heart finds in Him is so different than what another discovers, yet none less true.', 23301, 0), (120103, 'My heart can feel the softness of a starOnly when the moon stays afar I lay my mind on the pillow of skyWhere sleep dares not ever to pry', 2760, 0), (120104, 'I shall ever try to drive all evils away from my heart and keep my love in flower, knowing that thou hast thy seat in the inmost shrine of my heart.', 430, 0), (120105, 'The holiest of all holidays are thoseKept by ourselves in silence and apart', 23302, 0), (120106, 'IN the book of my heart, pages keep falling out, many of them marked "Mom and Dad.', 23303, 0), (120107, 'I don’t know exactly what life has in store for me, but my travels have helped me formulate a better idea of my immediate next move. Europe is where my heart lies, now; here in Paris, at a gallery or museum, or possibly Rome, where Alexander took me last winter.', 23304, 0), (120108, 'He may care for her, though she really has been almost rude to him at times. But she! – why, Margaret would never think of him, I’m sure! Such a thing has never entered her head.""Entering her heart would do.', 640, 0), (120109, 'A heartless Christian must be a terrible grief to our Lord.', 1903, 0), (120110, 'If you think deep inside yourself that you can not live except in the presence of someone that is not true, but this feeling remains true and this is more important than anything else .', 22053, 0), (120111, 'If you are filled with guilt and shame, it''s because your heart remembers God but your head seems to have forgotten Him.', 9420, 0), (120112, 'When a mother elevates her communication, she naturally elevates the outcomes of her child''s life since a mother''s words become her child''s universe of possibilities.', 7514, 0), (120113, 'My heart is a traitor,” the boy said to the alchemist, when they had paused to rest the horses. “It doesn’t want me to go on.” “That makes sense,” the alchemist answered. “Naturally it’s afraid that, in pursuing your dream, you might lose everything you’ve won.” “Well, then, why should I listen to my heart?” “Because you will never again be able to keep it quiet. Even if you pretend not to have heard what it tells you, it will always be there inside you, repeating to you what you’re thinking about life and about the world.” “You mean I should listen, even if it’s treasonous?” “Treason is a blow that comes unexpectedly. If you know your heart well, it will never be able to do that to you. Because you’ll know its dreams and wishes, and will know how to deal with them. “You will never be able to escape from your heart. So it’s better to listen to what it has to say. That way, you’ll never have to fear an unanticipated blow.', 34, 0), (120114, 'The only path that has any meaning is one that resolves your being in the feeling that your heart is empowered by doing what is necessary for your existence.', 20490, 0), (120115, 'I reside in an abode where your thoughts imagine me... You reside in my heart where the auricles camouflage my longing...', 5535, 0), (120116, 'A vision is something supernatural, which develops in the heart of a man', 3800, 0), (120117, 'The Holy Spirit puts ideas into the heart of the believer', 3800, 0), (120118, 'Listen to your heart into which the Holy Spirit has put the treasure He has for you', 3800, 0), (120119, 'Do not allow the vision to die in your heart', 3800, 0), (120120, 'Your vision is not only in your heart but also in the heart of God', 3800, 0), (120121, 'No need to try to explain to others what''s in your heart. Some things are just between you and God.', 5758, 0), (120122, 'I listen to my heart and mind when I plan the things, but I cannot support those, who do not listen to their heart and', 8499, 0), (120123, 'I am touched by your kindness and loving comments on how the messages from the Danish way of Parenting - which comes from my heart - have changed your and your children''s lives. Each and every one I keep in my personal treasure chest. Your support means everything.', 6348, 0), (120124, 'Maybe it wasn''t a good idea to rank the people in your life. That''s not how the heart worked. The heart didn''t make lists.', 186, 0), (120125, 'Sometime your heart is the only thing worth listening to.', 302, 0), (120126, 'Kindness is a lamp that we should always kindle in our heart. The warmth of it not only make us happy from inside and give light to others. But also makes the world a little more beautiful place everytime it lights the lamps in other hearts.', 9492, 0), (120127, 'I could be the drumbeat in your chest like madness before a storm swirling restlessly.', 7672, 0), (120128, 'Do not go to my grave. Mary knows, I am not there. Look for me in between pages and on people’s lips.Do not go to my old school. Do not go to my old house —I am not in any of those places. Look for me in your hearts and greet me there.', 3588, 0), (120129, 'His heart missed a beat and never regretted the lovely loss.', 76, 0), (120130, 'A heart grows flat and stale from too much thinking.', 884, 0), (120131, 'I crawled over the mountain of death, Watching the corpses roll down like the stones. Searching for the light which everyone always spoke of. I fought the wolves and also the death, and knocked the door, which already had a thousand handprints, soaked with blood. The door opened finally and I saw the light, which hit me in the heart and pushed me down the steep. I fell into the never ending pit, watching others crawl up the mountain in the search of light.', 9492, 0), (120132, 'I stared down at my hands and saw the blood coat them, how warm and real something felt when it wasn’t just ink and stains. This was life and I was holding it in my hands. I drew my eyes back up and beneath the flickering streetlight and the throng of drunken cattle, I saw nothing else but the dead girl. Somebody out there had taken her life, her heart, and there I was with her warm, sticky blood. Feeling the most alive I’d felt in years.I had to find him. I just had to.', 23305, 0), (120133, 'There was the world and there is you, where I belong clouds are more powerful than the sun.', 7743, 0), (120134, 'Stop treating your feelings like they are worth so little. I''m your heart, you idiot. Stop treating me like I''m worth so little. Choose me over your brain for once... Please...', 7609, 0), (120135, 'A feeling that He''s right here with you or that you''re miles apart, is the difference of a prayer with love, or with an absence of the heart.', 19349, 0), (120136, 'Love hides in all sorts of places, in the most sorrowful corner of your heart, in the darkest and most hopeless situation', 23306, 0), (120137, 'Some days I''m to sip you. Some days I''m to be drowned.', 12103, 0), (120138, 'The human heart is deeply nuanced who can know it? Taming the heart involves trust. What do you trust in? The material world has less substance than most people realize. We are made of stuff but this stuff is something that cannot be regarded as real. In a very real sense, you are a collection of your choices.', 7501, 0), (120139, 'My heart is my happy home.', 2878, 0), (120140, 'When you are brave enough to see me and accept me at my most basic, uninspired, unremarkable self – indeed, embrace my ordinariness - then, and only then, will you develop eyes to see the extraordinary splendor of my heart.', 6361, 0), (120141, 'Let your heart be your eye.', 2878, 0), (120142, 'When love is roaming in our mind, looping in the deepest fringes of our heart, undreamt spaciousness emerges, repealing the constraints of triviality and letting stifling narrowness fade away. While our mindset is besieged by a revolving burst of emotion, our world is ultimately opening up. (Cape of good hope)', 2711, 0), (120143, 'If your heart is your home, you can be happy anywhere.', 2878, 0), (120144, 'It''s a dreadful world with only your own heart to drive you.', 828, 0), (120145, 'I was meeting a mountain. I meant to kiss her in secret. I meant to wed her under the midnight dark. The prettiest mountain you ever saw, sparkling with snow in all the right places, rich with granite and tourmaline and silver, sturdy and sensible and weathered by experience of eons. When she saw me, my mountain''s pine trees bristled and the wind in her heights whistled my name. When I saw her, I felt rivers break through the rock of my heart and carve me into a new shape.', 828, 0), (120146, 'The passion in the heart of God is to be established', 3800, 0), (120147, 'There is a certain calling in your life from the heart of God', 3800, 0), (120148, 'Loving God is a display of the heart', 3800, 0), (120149, 'Love can only be generated from the depths of the human heart', 3800, 0), (120150, 'Let your heart be filled with passionate love that compelled Christ to give his life to you', 3800, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (120151, 'The state of our heart is very important in fulfilling our destiny', 3800, 0), (120152, 'Her eyes reversed into herself, to watch the secret heart of herself pounding itself into pieces against the side of her chest.', 567, 0), (120153, 'Merry Heart And Joy Is To Maintain Your Well Being', 3800, 0), (120154, 'A merciful heart beats contently stronger than many vengeful ones', 2760, 0), (120155, 'HereIt''s like the song of a family where everything''s always all right, it''s a song of belonging that makes you belong just by hearing it, it''s a song that''ll always take care of you and never leave you. If you have a heart, it breaks, if you have a heart that''s broken, it fixes.', 258, 0), (120156, 'Follow the trace of timeuntil the startcollapses with the endin the space of the heart.', 23307, 0), (120157, 'The heart is a sacred home.', 2878, 0), (120158, 'Life starts when you live for someones other than you, and ends when you stop living in others’ hearts! Birth & death are simply incidental.', 11317, 0), (120159, 'And just as he said of me, the thing that his heart desired was not the thing that he professed to want.', 3795, 0), (120160, 'Pause for a moment and prayerfully consider your response: What breaks your heart?', 3962, 0), (120161, 'What takes first place in your heart determines your pursuit', 3800, 0), (120162, 'Soft hearts make the universe worth living in.', 73, 0), (120163, 'An open mind and heart usually lead you to those who have the same.', 6353, 0), (120164, 'There''s something about water that washes away the cares of the mind and heart.', 8494, 0), (120165, 'I don’t have any fancy story,about the way we fell in love.It was that one awkward move,and the next I remember, I was looking at you.', 2965, 0), (120166, 'We must keep our heart open in the very moment our instinct tells us to shut it down. When we transcend this critical point, we are finally and truly able to deepen our