. Fitzwilliam Darcy.', 22494, 0), (120895, 'God wants you to always have a hunger in your heart to learn something new.', 3800, 0), (120896, 'Donate your blood from your heart to save life. Life will donate you hearts full of love, blood and contentment in return.', 2760, 0), (120897, 'The human heart is like india-rubber; a little swells it, but a great deal will not burst it.', 3187, 0), (120898, 'It’ll always be mine, but it’ll always be your heart.', 3805, 0), (120899, 'Hearts aren''t handcuffs and people aren''t prisons. When you feel it''s time for you to leave, you leave. You neither need to wait to be released, nor ask for permission.', 8694, 0), (120900, 'Tears only dry up as a result of hardness of the heart, and the hearts only harden as a result of frequent sinning.', 1225, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (120901, 'I breathe in...the silenceof my own heartaching with tendernesswith memories..Of home.', 1864, 0), (120902, 'To know God, know your heart (conscience). After you know your heart, you will learn to see God in all things. Truth can only be seen by those with Truth in them.', 2678, 0), (120903, 'Stay strong; disappointments will not stay for that long. Wipe away your tears; be ready to receive cheers from people all over the world, beginning from you!', 3301, 0), (120904, 'Touch with your heart more than with your hands.', 920, 0), (120905, 'You’ve jerked my heart more than your dick.', 953, 0), (120906, 'Love is the reflection of a broken heart in a shattered mirror...', 5034, 0), (120907, 'Truth is first felt in the heart before the mind. Those who try looking for truth through the mind before the heart will never find Truth.', 2678, 0), (120908, 'Get out of my head,You''ve overstayed your stay,This head no longer can spare more thoughts,Leave my aching heart alone,You weaved your web all over my heart,Captured what was never yours,The aching in my chest can''t bare more,Get out of here,My soul is no longer a safe place.', 8667, 0), (120909, 'What is a goal without a purpose?', 9207, 0), (120910, 'Affection is invaluable. I will accept your heart as payment and change your mind.', 6509, 0), (120911, 'Do not try to lead men who are unwilling to follow you; if their heart is not in it, you will never find the old spirit or the old courage.', 23413, 0), (120912, 'Many have balls but only a few have heart.', 953, 0), (120913, 'When you see, not only intellectually but with your heart too, how we are all connected, how can you harm another? It''s the same as harming oneself.', 23414, 0), (120914, 'My heart beats so hard, I feel like I have an earthquake inside of me. It''s weighing me down and my hands shake with the need of safety and comfort.', 920, 0), (120915, 'Dreaming of another time,Dreaming of cla